cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the generation of automata from LTL formulas using logical reasoning and disambiguation procedures. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the generation of automata from formal languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for automata generation, which can be seen as a programming language problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper introduces optimizations and simplifications on the intermediate representation of the automata. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the application of the generated automata in the analysis of Markov chains, which is a common problem in AI.
